{{also|Minimum}}
==English==

===Etymology===
{{PIE root|en|mey}}
From {{etyl|la|en}} {{m|la|minimum}}, neuter form of {{m|la|minimus||least, smallest}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{audio|En-us-minimum.ogg|Audio (US)|lang=en}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|minima|s}}

# The [[lowest]] [[limit]].
#: ''We prefer candidates with a '''minimum''' of 4 years experience in the field.''
#: ''We need a '''minimum''' of 3 fully-qualified staff members on duty at all time.''
# The [[smallest]] [[amount]].
#: ''He always tries to get away with doing the '''minimum'''.''
#: ''Please keep noise to a '''minimum''' after 11 o'clock''
# {{label|en|astronomy}} A period of minimum [[brightness]] or [[energy]] [[intensity]] (of a [[star]]).
#: {{ux|en|The Maunder '''minimum''' of the Sun reportedly corresponded to a period of great cold on Earth.}}
# {{label|en|analysis}} A [[lower bound]] of a set which is also an element of that set.
# {{label|en|statistics}} The smallest member of a [[batch]] or [[sample]] or the lower bound of a [[probability distribution]].

====Usage notes====
* {{m|en|minima|Minima}} is more common plural for the technical senses.

